00:14:58,326 --> 00:15:02,091
Second of all, it will become difficult
to have the availability

240
00:15:02,091 --> 00:15:06,910
of high-power sources
at such increasingly high frequencies.

241
00:15:07,530 --> 00:15:10,555
In fact, as we said, 
the fundamental frequency

242
00:15:10,555 --> 00:15:15,425
for a 3-4 teslas device
is of the order of 100 GHz.

243
00:15:17,597 --> 00:15:20,103
If we take the second harmonic,

244
00:15:20,103 --> 00:15:23,407
that will be 200 GHz,

245
00:15:23,407 --> 00:15:25,758
which is already quite difficult
for a high-power source.

246
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:29,018
What kind of power sources 
do we have in this range?

247
00:15:29,682 --> 00:15:32,026
This is illustrated in the picture

248
00:15:32,448 --> 00:15:35,363
where we can see the power
that sources can provide

249
00:15:35,946 --> 00:15:37,481
on a logarithmic scale,

250
00:15:38,550 --> 00:15:43,864
see, 100, 10 kilowatt and 1 megawatt,
as a function of the frequency.

251
00:15:45,257 --> 00:15:47,242
100 GHZ is in this range,

252
00:15:47,242 --> 00:15:49,892
where we can see that the power
that can be provided

253
00:15:49,892 --> 00:15:54,575
by relatively simple 
and conventional sources

254
00:15:54,575 --> 00:15:58,839
such as the traveling wave tube 
amplifier [TWT] or the Magnetron

255
00:15:58,839 --> 00:16:01,472
or the Klystron
is actually very, very small.

256
00:16:01,472 --> 00:16:06,403
We're not yet in the frequency range
where lasers can provide power,

257
00:16:06,403 --> 00:16:08,036
so what can we have as a source?

258
00:16:08,036 --> 00:16:09,878
We have something 
that's called a gyrotron.

259
00:16:09,878 --> 00:16:12,050
That's typically a source that covers

260
00:16:13,198 --> 00:16:18,503
the 10 to 100, 150, 200 GHz
range of frequency.

261
00:16:19,025 --> 00:16:20,277
What is a gyrotron?

262
00:16:20,277 --> 00:16:24,464
Let's look at the basic principles
behind its functioning

263
00:16:24,464 --> 00:16:25,774
in very simple terms.

264
00:16:26,585 --> 00:16:30,338
The function is based on the so-called
cyclotron resonance master instability,

265
00:16:30,338 --> 00:16:33,992
which is a relativistic effect
associated with the bunching

266
00:16:33,992 --> 00:16:37,847
of the electron motion
as they gyrate around the field lines.

267
00:16:37,847 --> 00:16:40,982
There are three essential 
components in a gyrotron.

268
00:16:40,982 --> 00:16:43,593
There's an electron beam that's annular,

269
00:16:44,023 --> 00:16:47,683
which is produced by a cathode,

270
00:16:48,618 --> 00:16:52,070
here, illustrated by this shadowed area,

271
00:16:52,718 --> 00:16:56,152
the electron beam propagates
in the axial direction here

272
00:16:56,152 --> 00:17:00,446
guided by a strong magnetic field
which is produced by the coils

273
00:17:00,446 --> 00:17:04,542
of which we see the cross-sections here,
which again confines the electrons

274
00:17:04,542 --> 00:17:07,948
but also determines the frequency
at which they gyrate

275
00:17:08,488 --> 00:17:09,680
around the field lines.

276
00:17:10,444 --> 00:17:15,501
Where the electron beam propagates
and where the magnetic field is produced

277
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:19,198
and where it's actually flat
in its intensity,

278
00:17:19,814 --> 00:17:21,738
we have a resonant cavity.

279
00:17:21,738 --> 00:17:25,738
That's the third component 
of the gyrotron.

280
00:17:26,358 --> 00:17:29,845
It's essentially a cylinder
with a smoothly varying cross-section

281
00:17:30,519 --> 00:17:32,949
and its resonant cavity allows
resonant interaction

282
00:17:32,949 --> 00:17:35,459
between the electrons 
and the modes in the cavity —

283
00:17:35,459 --> 00:17:37,445
again, wave-particle resonance.

284
00:17:37,445 --> 00:17:41,608
The same kind that we are 
actually using, in some sense,

285
00:17:41,608 --> 00:17:44,664
to heat the plasma
once the wave is launched into it.

286
00:17:45,629 --> 00:17:48,415
So what remains to be done
is simply to extract the energy

287
00:17:48,415 --> 00:17:51,038
from this cavity using a window

288
00:17:51,038 --> 00:17:56,545
in the form of a particular polarization
for an electromagnetic wave

289
00:17:56,545 --> 00:18:00,804
that will propagate in waveguides 
all the way to our tokamak plasma.

290
00:18:02,244 --> 00:18:04,666
Naturally, we need to dump the energy

291
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:08,666
of the remaining electrons

292
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:13,297
that have passed through the cavity
and that have provided their energy

293
00:18:13,297 --> 00:18:14,762
or part of their energy

294
00:18:14,762 --> 00:18:17,584
to the electromagnetic wave in the cavity.

295
00:18:17,595 --> 00:18:22,557
Here we see a broken view
of the gyrotron — its layout.

296
00:18:22,557 --> 00:18:26,253
Once again, there's a cathode
on this side, the annular beam,

297
00:18:26,253 --> 00:18:29,630
which is now represented
in a yellow color;

298
00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:36,085
the guiding magnetic field,
which is produced

299
00:18:36,085 --> 00:18:38,265
by a superconducting coil, typically;

300
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:42,401
the resonant cavity;
and the output window,

301
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:45,423
through which we extract
the electromagnetic wave

302
00:18:46,043 --> 00:18:47,631
in the form of a beam.

303
00:18:48,331 --> 00:18:52,490
The window typically needs to allow

304
00:18:54,190 --> 00:18:56,386
close to 100% of the power 
to be extracted,

305
00:18:56,386 --> 00:19:00,565
so it has to absorb very low amounts 
of the microwave power

306
00:19:00,565 --> 00:19:04,815
and typically is made
of a CVD diamond.

307
00:19:06,287 --> 00:19:11,283
Then we of course have
the collector that collects the electrons

308
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:13,216
and their remaining energy.

309
00:19:13,216 --> 00:19:16,905
Let's look at the layout
of an existing ECRH system —

310
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:20,308
that's the system that we have
on the TCV tokamak in Lausanne.

311
00:19:20,999 --> 00:19:24,499
There are two kinds of sources
at two different frequencies,

312
00:19:24,499 --> 00:19:28,676
although all of them are gyrotrons,
we can see here the different sources

313
00:19:28,676 --> 00:19:34,167
installed tens of meters away
from the tokamak

314
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:39,544
and connected to the tokamak
by oversized, overmoded waveguides

315
00:19:39,544 --> 00:19:43,596
which guarantee the transport
of the wave energy

316
00:19:43,596 --> 00:19:45,216
with very low amounts of losses.

317
00:19:45,216 --> 00:19:48,960
Then there is an injection
of the wave energy

318
00:19:49,630 --> 00:19:51,540
into the tokamak plasma.

319
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:56,421
More specifically, to give you an idea
of the parameters of the ECRH system,

320
00:19:57,737 --> 00:20:00,762
we have two subsystems.

321
00:20:01,587 --> 00:20:06,036
The one at the second harmonic X-mode,
this is exactly the schema

322
00:20:06,036 --> 00:20:10,208
of operation we illustrated
in simple terms a few minutes ago.

323
00:20:10,826 --> 00:20:12,744
We refer to that as X2.

324
00:20:13,201 --> 00:20:16,598
The actual frequency is about 83 gigaherz.

325
00:20:17,625 --> 00:20:21,271
There are six sources at this frequency,

326
00:20:21,271 --> 00:20:25,974
each one having half a megawatt,
and we inject their power

327
00:20:26,469 --> 00:20:29,200
through side launchers,

328
00:20:30,096 --> 00:20:34,505
both to heat the plasma
in determined locations

329
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:36,423
inside the tokamak,

330
00:20:36,423 --> 00:20:41,623
and to launch waves
with a particular direction,

331
00:20:41,623 --> 00:20:44,450
therefore to drive a current
in the plasma,

332
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:49,317
which we refer to as the ECCD scheme —
electron cyclotron current drive scheme.

333
00:20:49,863 --> 00:20:52,627
Second harmonic X-mode 
has a cutoff density

334
00:20:52,627 --> 00:20:56,869
of a few times 10¹⁹ per cubic meter.

335
00:20:56,869 --> 00:20:59,729
If we see the top view
of the injection points of the tokamak,

336
00:20:59,729 --> 00:21:04,964
we can see that by moving
the steering mirror,

337
00:21:04,964 --> 00:21:08,658
we can in fact give an angle
to the injection of the wave

338
00:21:09,098 --> 00:21:11,508
and determine the propagation
in one direction or the other

339
00:21:11,508 --> 00:21:14,736
and therefore determine,
also, current drive

340
00:21:14,736 --> 00:21:16,071
in one direction or the other.

341
00:21:16,071 --> 00:21:19,480
Current drive can be off-axis
or on-axis depending,

342
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:23,813
again, on the choice 
of the injection geometry.

343
00:21:24,936 --> 00:21:27,266
The second subsystem that we have

344
00:21:27,266 --> 00:21:30,637
is the system working
at the third harmonic X-mode,

345
00:21:31,138 --> 00:21:33,147
referred to as X3.

346
00:21:33,519 --> 00:21:36,946
The frequency is 
in this case 118 GHz.

347
00:21:37,888 --> 00:21:41,863
We have so far 3 sources
of half a megawatt each.

348
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:44,694
They are injected from the top.

349
00:21:45,787 --> 00:21:48,348
As I said before 
in very qualitative terms,

350
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:50,750
as we increase the harmonic number,

351
00:21:50,756 --> 00:21:54,018
so as we go higher and higher
in frequency,

352
00:21:54,018 --> 00:21:56,509
the absorption efficiency
is less and less.

353
00:21:56,509 --> 00:22:01,520
That's exactly why we inject from the top,
so we have actually more plasma

354
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:05,633
to go through in order 
for the absorption to reach good levels,

355
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:07,326
even at the third harmonic.

356
00:22:07,772 --> 00:22:10,986
The advantage of the third harmonic 
is that its cutoff density,

357
00:22:10,986 --> 00:22:15,638
the density above which
the wave cannot penetrate to the core,

358
00:22:15,638 --> 00:22:20,599
is higher, about 1.2 x 10²⁰
per cubic meter.

359
00:22:21,113 --> 00:22:26,691
So we do inject these waves,
first of all to heat the plasma,

360
00:22:27,536 --> 00:22:29,489
and how does plasma respond?

361
00:22:29,489 --> 00:22:32,547
I'd like to show just one
very simple example.

362
00:22:32,547 --> 00:22:35,547
This is the profile 
of the electron temperature,

363
00:22:35,547 --> 00:22:37,816
expressed in millions of degrees.

364
00:22:39,277 --> 00:22:42,986
In the ohmic situation,
that is the plasma which is only heated

365
00:22:42,986 --> 00:22:45,749
by the electrical current flowing in it,

366
00:22:45,749 --> 00:22:50,642
we have a fairly low and even 
a fairly flat temperature profile.

367
00:22:51,338 --> 00:22:55,160
If we inject these waves
at the second harmonic or the X-mode,

368
00:22:55,198 --> 00:23:00,191
then we have very big 
and very high-profile,

369
00:23:00,191 --> 00:23:03,961
reaching values above 150 million degrees.

370
00:23:04,251 --> 00:23:07,152
Another important point
that was discovered

371
00:23:07,152 --> 00:23:12,802
in a number of experiments including TCV
is that using ECRH power,

372
00:23:13,747 --> 00:23:16,596
locally deposited in
particular points in a plasma

373
00:23:16,596 --> 00:23:21,868
some instabilities can be controlled 
or even suppressed completely.

374
00:23:22,419 --> 00:23:25,326
That's the case 
of the so-called tearing modes,

375
00:23:25,951 --> 00:23:30,929
which are instabilities that develop
in the core of the plasma

376
00:23:31,477 --> 00:23:35,799
and provide a change even in 
the topology of the plasma,

377
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:38,909
creating islands in the magnetic 
fields inside the plasma,

378
00:23:38,919 --> 00:23:45,146
therefore leading to a loss of heat
from the core of the plasma.

379
00:23:45,476 --> 00:23:51,407
You can see in this movie
that this instability can develop

380
00:23:51,407 --> 00:23:55,642
in the TCV tokamak 
and can actually lead

381
00:23:55,642 --> 00:23:57,587
to a degradation of its performance.

382
00:23:58,388 --> 00:24:02,147
The point is that if we can inject
a microwave beam

383
00:24:02,947 --> 00:24:09,153
exactly on top of that instability —
the details of interaction

384
00:24:09,153 --> 00:24:15,000
between the beam and the magnetic island
are too complicated to be discussed

385
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:20,674
in this course — we can actually eliminate
this instability, eliminate this bubble

386
00:24:20,674 --> 00:24:23,386
that leads to a degradation of performance.

387
00:24:23,890 --> 00:24:29,671
Let's now look at the ECRH system
as it is being developed for ITER.

