00:30:22,714 --> 00:30:28,375
so that's not the system that's foreseen
for the first stage of the ITER operation.

476
00:30:29,330 --> 00:30:32,445
Also, with a power 
of about 20 MW

477
00:30:32,445 --> 00:30:35,429
and a frequency corresponding 
to the lower hybrid wave

478
00:30:35,429 --> 00:30:38,381
in the core of the ITER plasma 
of about 5 GHz.

479
00:30:40,972 --> 00:30:44,490
Finally, we are also preparing
an ECRH system

480
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:48,845
which will have 24 MW of power,

481
00:30:48,845 --> 00:30:49,845
as we have seen,

482
00:30:49,845 --> 00:30:52,266
at a frequency 170 GHz,

483
00:30:52,266 --> 00:30:55,229
and the reason I put this in green,
is that this is the only system

484
00:30:55,229 --> 00:31:00,341
that would be needed
for day 1 of the ITER operation.

485
00:31:01,807 --> 00:31:04,173
We are now ready to very briefly
summarize this lecture.

486
00:31:04,173 --> 00:31:09,903
We have seen that ECRH waves
are used to heat bulk electrons

487
00:31:09,903 --> 00:31:11,923
and to drive current in the plasma.

488
00:31:12,998 --> 00:31:18,564
The high frequency of these waves
leads to quasi-optical properties of them,

489
00:31:18,564 --> 00:31:22,489
and to local absorption,
which is essential for heating,

490
00:31:22,489 --> 00:31:26,784
for driving current, and for controlling
instabilities in the plasma.

491
00:31:27,729 --> 00:31:30,899
There is no need for in-vessel antennas,
so all the problems we have discussed

492
00:31:30,899 --> 00:31:35,636
for ICRH and lower hybrid 
waves are overcome.

493
00:31:37,381 --> 00:31:41,040
Of course, the ECRH system
is foreseen in ITER —

494
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:43,050
for ionizing the plasma to begin with,

495
00:31:43,050 --> 00:31:45,802
for heating the plasma,
for driving current in the plasma,

496
00:31:45,802 --> 00:31:49,362
and most importantly
for controlling these instabilities.
